Option Explicit Dim WeekCol As Long Dim InvRow As Long Dim PlnRow As Long Dim CoverWk As Long Dim WorkHRS As Long Dim TargetEff As Double Sub FastBalance()     Dim ws As Worksheet     Dim lastCol As Long     Dim shortageRow As Long     Set ws = ActiveSheet     Application.ScreenUpdating = False     Application.EnableEvents = False     Application.Calculation = xlCalculationManual     ' ===== INITIAL FULL RECALC =====     Application.CalculateFull     ' ===== SETTINGS =====     WeekCol = CLng(ws.Cells(3, 15).Value)     PlnRow = CLng(ws.Cells(7, 15).Value)     InvRow = CLng(ws.Cells(6, 15).Value)     CoverWk = CLng(ws.Cells(8, 15).Value)     WorkHRS = CLng(ws.Cells(5, 15).Value)     TargetEff = CDbl(ws.Cells(9, 15).Value)     lastCol = ws.Cells(11, ws.Columns.Count).End(xlToLeft).Column     ' ===== MAIN LOOP =====     Do While WeekCol <= lastCol         shortageRow = FindNearestShortage(ws, WeekCol, lastCol)         ' No more shortages         If shortageRow = 0 Then Exit Do         ' Skip week if no work hours         If ws.Cells(WorkHRS, WeekCol).Value = 0 Then             WeekCol = WeekCol + 1             GoTo NextLoop         End If         ' Check efficiency availability         If ws.Cells(10, WeekCol).Value > TargetEff Then             ' Add production             ws.Cells(shortageRow + 2, WeekCol).Value = _             ws.Cells(shortageRow + 2, WeekCol).Value + 40             ' Recalculate ONLY current sheet             ws.Calculate             ' Efficiency exceeded?             If ws.Cells(10, WeekCol).Value < TargetEff Then                 ' Undo addition                 ws.Cells(shortageRow + 2, WeekCol).Value = _                 ws.Cells(shortageRow + 2, WeekCol).Value - 40                 ws.Calculate                 ' Still shortage exists?                 If ws.Cells(shortageRow, WeekCol).Value < 0 Then                     MsgBox _                     "STOPPED: Efficiency limit reached while shortage still exists." & vbCrLf & vbCrLf & _                     "Part: " & ws.Cells(shortageRow - 1, 2).Value & vbCrLf & _                     "Week: " & WeekCol & vbCrLf & _                     "Remaining Shortage: " & ws.Cells(shortageRow, WeekCol).Value, _                     vbCritical, _                     "Planning Stopped"                     GoTo SafeExit                 End If                 WeekCol = WeekCol + 1             End If         Else             WeekCol = WeekCol + 1         End If NextLoop:     Loop     MsgBox "Balance Finished Successfully", vbInformation SafeExit:     Application.Calculation = xlCalculationAutomatic     Application.ScreenUpdating = True     Application.EnableEvents = True End Sub Function FindNearestShortage(ws As Worksheet, currentWeek As Long, lastCol As Long) As Long     Dim chkWeek As Long     Dim chkRow As Long     Dim lastRow As Long     lastRow = ws.Cells(ws.Rows.Count, 3).End(xlUp).Row     For chkWeek = currentWeek To lastCol         chkRow = InvRow         Do While chkRow <= lastRow             If IsNumeric(ws.Cells(chkRow, chkWeek).Value) Then                 If ws.Cells(chkRow, chkWeek).Value < 0 Then                     ' Highlight near shortages                     If (chkWeek - currentWeek) < CoverWk Then                         ws.Cells(chkRow + 2, currentWeek).Font.Color = RGB(255, 0, 0)                     End If                     FindNearestShortage = chkRow                     Exit Function                 End If             End If             chkRow = chkRow + 7         Loop     Next chkWeek     FindNearestShortage = 0 End Function
